# UPDATE.LOG — Project Veyra

---

## v0.0.2 BETA (21 June 2026)

### Backend Systems
- Added JWT authentication (register, login, session validation)
- Added unique username system (case-insensitive check)
- Added player database with persistent storage (JSON-based)
- Added 0G Storage integration (proof generation, upload, verify, state save/load)
- Added SoulMaiden system (resonance, gifts, AI conversations)
- Added Combat engine (attack, heal, flee, skill usage, item drops)
- Added Marketplace (list, buy, cancel, VS-to-VEYA exchange)
- Added Quest system (accept, progress, complete with rewards)
- Added Chronicle & Leaderboard APIs
- Added Socket.IO multiplayer (position sync, combat updates, notifications)

### Frontend Integration
- Added auth screens (login/register) with styled UI
- Added auth.js module (full API client for all endpoints)
- Added socket.js module (Socket.IO client wrapper)
- Updated main.js with server integration flow:
  - Auth check on boot → login/register → character creation → play
  - Socket connected on game start
  - Auto-save to server every 15 seconds
  - Lyra NPC talk via server API
  - Monster/combat socket events handled
- Fixed API endpoint mismatches (create-character → player/create, etc.)

### Infrastructure
- Express server serves frontend static files
- Single process: backend + frontend on port 8790
- .env configuration (JWT_SECRET, PORT)
- .gitignore (node_modules, .env, *.db)

